This paper is about Spoken Language Understanding (SLU), which is a subfield of Natural Language Processing (NLP) that deals with understanding spoken language. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which includes papers on NLP and speech processing. 

The paper also proposes a recurrent neural network (RNN) based incremental processing approach, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). 

Additionally, the paper discusses the use of an automatic speech recognition (ASR) module, which is related to signal processing (cs.SD). 

Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed approach on a benchmark dataset, which is related to experimental design and analysis (cs.EX). However, since this is a less specific category, it is less likely than the other categories mentioned.
